extends basic_changelog

append new_features
    ul
        li
            | Added <strong>-safe</strong> switch and
            | <strong>module(system) Identifier;</strong> syntax.
        li Added range support to foreach statement.
        li
            | <strong>scope</strong> parameter storage class means the
            | parameter will not 'escape' the scope of the function
            | invocation. Using this for delegate parameters will prevent
            | some closure allocations by the calling function.
        li
            | The lazy storage class now implies <strong>scope</strong>
            | so that lazy arguments won't trigger a heap allocated closure.
        li
            | The 'this' parameter to struct member functions is now a
            | reference type, rather than a pointer.
            | <em>This breaks existing code</em>.

    p More changes to druntime:

    table.change-table
        thead
            tr
                th from
                th to
        tbody
            tr
                td OutOfMemoryException
                td OutOfMemoryError
            tr
                td SwitchException
                td SwitchError
            tr
                td HiddenFuncException
                td HiddenFuncError
            tr
                td ArrayBoundsException
                td RangeError
            tr
                td AssertException
                td AssertError
            tr
                td FinalizeException
                td FinalizeError
            tr
                td onArrayBoundsError
                td onRangeError
            tr
                td stdc.*
                td core.stdc.*
            tr
                td sys.*
                td core.sys.*
    ul
        li
            | Added core.runtime.loadLibrary() as an experimental feature
            | for loading dynamic libraries (Win32 only at the moment).
        li
            | Added core.runtime.unloadLibrary() as an experimental feature
            | for unloading dynamic libraries previously loaded by
            | loadLibrary().
        li
            | core.thread.sleep() accepts a long integer specifying
            | the sleep interval in 100 nanosecond intervals
            | (the previous release notes said this was a float, IIRC).
        li
            | It is no longer necessary to link in druntime separately,
            | it is inserted into libphobos2.a.

append bugs_fixed
